# Branch Strategy (Mandatory)

Use this strategy for every code change.

## Branch format

`<team>-<developer>-<type>/<ticket>-<short-slug>`

- `team`: `frontend`, `backend`, or `repo`
- `developer`: PR owner username
- `type`: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `docs`, `chore`, `perf`, `build`, `ci`
- `ticket`: issue id when available (recommended)

Examples:
- `frontend-envy-feat/GC-142-dashboard-cards`
- `backend-envy-fix/GC-209-auth-cookie-expiry`
- `repo-envy-chore/engineering-standards`

## PR routing

- `frontend-*` branches must target `main-frontend`
- `backend-*` branches must target `main-backend`
- `repo-*` branches for shared workflow, docs, CI, or repo-wide standards may target `main` by pull request
- Do not push directly to `main`

## PR title format

`[<team>][<developer>][<type>] <short-title>`

Example:
- `[backend][envy][fix] Better Auth session expiry handling`
